    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="532"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d532">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.0144/98</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fletcher</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1063</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 28, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to the Department’s telegram No.
                    1047 of May 8, 7 p.m., relative to an attack made on May 1 by armed Mexicans on
                    an American patrol in the Big Bend district, I have the honor to report that in
                    reply to the Embassy’s representations, the Mexican Foreign Office states in a
                    note dated the 17th instant, that the group of armed men referred to were
                    outlaws, and that the Mexican Government has issued appropriate orders to pursue
                    them actively.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry P. Fletcher</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
